text: Dillingham Census Area is a census area in the U.S. state of Alaska. As of the 2020 census, the population was 4,857. It is part of the Unorganized Borough and therefore has no borough seat. Its largest community by far is the city of Dillingham, on a small arm of Bristol Bay on the Bering Sea. == References == Category:Alaska census areas
title: Dillingham Census Area, Alaska
